-- Air France, BNP Paribas, Roche: European Equity Preview
-- B y   J o s e p h   C i o l l i
-- 2012-04-03T04:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-03/air-france-bnp-paribas-roche-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in  European (SXXP)  (SXXP) trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The  Stoxx Europe 600 Index (SXXP)  rose 1.5 percent to 267.16. The
 Stoxx 50 Index (SX5P)  increased 1.6 percent to 2,496.78. The  Euro Stoxx
50 Index (SX5E) , a benchmark measure for nations using the euro, gained
1 percent to 2,501.18.  Air France-KLM (AF)  :  Europe ’s biggest airline said it
will extend a cost-cutting program introduced at bases in
southern France to flights from Paris Orly airport in a push to
return short-haul services to profit. The shares fell 1.2
percent to 4.21 euros.  BNP Paribas SA (BNP)  : Joachim von Schorlemer, country
head for Germany, left France’s largest bank after differences
over strategy, Handelsblatt said, citing a BNP spokesman. The
shares increased 0.4 percent to 35.70 euros.  Roche Holding AG (ROG)  : The world’s biggest maker of
cancer drugs’ $6.7 billion hostile takeover offer for  Illumina
Inc. (ILMN)  was rejected by the San Diego-based company’s board, which
said that the bid “dramatically undervalues” the company. The
shares gained 2.5 percent to 161 Swiss francs.  To contact the reporter on this story:
